57/cheney-cemetery","hooker_connections":["H03350","I00355"],"notes":"Manchester Connecticut cemetery associated with the Cheney silk-manufacturing family. Burial site of Walter Hooker Olcott (H03350, 1867-1936) and his wife Adeline Louise Cheney Olcott (I00355, 1870-1955) — the marriage that brought the Olcott agricultural-line and Cheney silk-manufacturing-line families together in Manchester."},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[{"type":"naming_pattern","related_id":"H00708","link_text":"Walter Hooker Olcott (1802-1832)","display_label":"Named after his great-granduncle who died young","slug":"walter-olcott-1802"}]}